1
00:00:05,272 --> 00:00:07,205
<i>[ Broots ]</i>
<i>IT'S JAROD'S LAST LAIR.</i>
<i>WE KNOW THAT MUCH.</i>

2
00:00:07,274 --> 00:00:10,208
HOW LONG SINCE HE LEFT?
IT'S ABOUT 24 HOURS.

3
00:00:10,277 --> 00:00:12,778
WE GOT A CLEAN-UP CREW
TAKIN' THE PLACE APART
AS WE SPEAK.

4
00:00:12,846 --> 00:00:14,879
SAME OLD SONG AND DANCE.

5
00:00:14,948 --> 00:00:17,049
YEAH.

6
00:00:24,725 --> 00:00:26,991
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>
<i>WHO'S THE EGGHEAD</i>
<i>IN THE GO-CART?</i>

7
00:00:27,060 --> 00:00:30,928
- THAT'S DR. GUCHI TUCHEN.
- THE NEW HEAD OF THE CENTRE'S
CLEAN-UP UNIT.

8
00:00:30,997 --> 00:00:34,165
<i>CREDENTIALS IMPECCABLE.</i>
YEAH, HE'S FROM CALCUTTA.

9
00:00:34,234 --> 00:00:36,367
REMIND ME TO CANCEL
THE FROZEN STEAKS FOR CHRISTMAS.

10
00:00:36,436 --> 00:00:38,670
<i> AH, DR. TUCHEN.</i>
<i> THIS IS--</i>

11
00:00:38,739 --> 00:00:41,240
THE INFAMOUS MISS PARKER.

12
00:00:41,308 --> 00:00:43,775
- EXCUSE ME FOR NOT STANDING.
- NOT A PROBLEM.

13
00:00:43,844 --> 00:00:47,612
<i> SO, WHAT DID</i>
<i> OUR LITTLE GENIUS LEAVE US</i>
<i> TO CLEAN UP THIS TIME?</i>

14
00:00:47,681 --> 00:00:50,415
I'M AFRAID IT'S A BIT
DISTURBING IN NATURE.

15
00:00:50,484 --> 00:00:52,718
HOW SO?

16
00:00:56,257 --> 00:00:58,190
HERE.

17
00:01:00,227 --> 00:01:03,262
- P.C.P.
- RIDICULOUS.
JAROD WOULDN'T USE DRUGS.

18
00:01:03,330 --> 00:01:05,797
I'M AFRAID I WILL HAVE
TO DISAGREE.

19
00:01:05,866 --> 00:01:09,601
WE RAN A SERIES OF FIELD TESTS
ON THE BLOOD RESIDUAL
OF THE SYRINGES,

20
00:01:09,670 --> 00:01:12,136
AND IT MATCHED
JAROD'S PERFECTLY.

21
00:01:12,205 --> 00:01:13,905
<i>[ Sydney ]</i>
<i>WITH WHAT JAROD'S BEEN THROUGH,</i>

22
00:01:13,973 --> 00:01:16,742
<i>ADDICTION IS</i>
<i>A DISTINCT POSSIBILITY.</i>

23
00:01:16,810 --> 00:01:19,478
- JAROD'S A JUNKIE?
- WE ALSO FOUND THIS.

24
00:01:22,649 --> 00:01:24,716
IT'S JAROD'S WRITING.

25
00:01:24,785 --> 00:01:27,385
<i>[ Broots ]</i>
<i>WHAT, DO YOU THINK</i>
<i>HE LEFT IT HERE BY ACCIDENT?</i>

26
00:01:27,454 --> 00:01:29,620
MAYBE HE REALLY IS CAUGHT UP
IN SOME KIND OF DRUG HAZE.

27
00:01:34,161 --> 00:01:37,396
<i>[ Man Over Walkie-Talkie,</i>
<i>  Indistinct ]</i>

28
00:01:37,465 --> 00:01:40,632
<i>[ Chattering ]</i>

29
00:01:40,701 --> 00:01:43,435
<i> WE GOT ONE OVER HERE</i>
<i> ALREADY IN THE BUILDING.</i>

30
00:01:43,504 --> 00:01:45,804
I DON'T KNOW WHAT HE'S ON,
BUT YOU'RE GONNA HAVE
TO LOCK HIM DOWN.

31
00:01:45,873 --> 00:01:47,972
- HOW'S YOUR PERSONAL
INJURY INSURANCE?
- PAID IN FULL.

32
00:01:48,041 --> 00:01:50,675
<i> NO ONE'S GONNA HURT YA.</i>
<i> WE JUST WANNA MAKE SURE</i>
<i> YOU'RE OKAY.</i>

33
00:01:50,744 --> 00:01:53,845
LET'S DO THIS EASY,
OKAY, PAL? COME ON.
EASY.

34
00:01:53,913 --> 00:01:57,649
<i> OKAY, LET'S GO.</i>
<i> NICE AND EASY.</i>
<i> NICE AND EASY.</i>

35
00:01:57,718 --> 00:02:00,485
[ Grunting ]

36
00:02:03,590 --> 00:02:05,590
COME ON!
NO! NO!

37
00:02:05,659 --> 00:02:09,127
MOMMY! NO! NO!
MOMMY!

38
00:02:09,196 --> 00:02:12,764
DAD! NO!
GRAB HIS FEET!

39
00:02:12,833 --> 00:02:14,833
MOMMY! DADDY!

40
00:02:14,902 --> 00:02:19,003
DON'T LET THEM TAKE ME!
[ Yelling ]

41
00:02:19,072 --> 00:02:22,207
<i>[ Man Narrating ]</i>
<i>THERE ARE PRETENDERS AMONG US.</i>

42
00:02:22,276 --> 00:02:24,209
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>
<i>I WAS TAKEN FROM MY FAMILY.</i>

43
00:02:24,278 --> 00:02:27,846
<i>THIRTY-SIX HOURS AND HE'S</i>
<i>ALREADY DEMONSTRATING MORE</i>
<i>TALENT THAN ANY OF OUR OTHERS.</i>

44
00:02:27,915 --> 00:02:31,316
<i>HOW MANY PEOPLE DIED</i>
<i>BECAUSE OF WHAT I THOUGHT UP?</i>

45
00:02:31,385 --> 00:02:34,820
SINCE I BROKE OUT,
I'VE SPENT EVERY MOMENT
SEARCHING FOR MY PAST.

46
00:02:34,889 --> 00:02:37,088
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>
<i>HE'S A PRETENDER--</i>

47
00:02:37,157 --> 00:02:39,925
<i>A GENIUS WHO CAN BECOME</i>
<i>ANYONE THAT HE WANTS TO BE.</i>

48
00:02:39,994 --> 00:02:42,727
-<i> THE CENTRE WANTS HIM ALIVE.</i>
- PREFERABLY.

49
00:02:42,796 --> 00:02:45,730
<i>- [ Miss Parker ] HE DEFENDS</i>
<i>  THE WEAK AND ABUSED.</i>
<i>- [ Jarod ] LIFE'S A GIFT.</i>

50
00:02:57,510 --> 00:02:59,978
-<i> YOU A DOCTOR?</i>
- I AM TODAY.

51
00:03:05,719 --> 00:03:08,186
[ Siren Wails ]
<i>[ Police Radio, Indistinct ]</i>

52
00:03:10,391 --> 00:03:12,524
[ Grunting ]
COME ON!

53
00:03:19,533 --> 00:03:22,267
- WHO DO WE GOT?
- TROUBLE. YOU'D BETTER KEEP
BOTH EYES ON THIS ONE.

54
00:03:26,206 --> 00:03:28,306
<i>WELCOME TO VISTA HOUSE,</i>
<i>MR. JONES.</i>

55
00:03:28,375 --> 00:03:30,942
I'M DR. EARL.
I AM YOUR STAFF PSYCHOLOGIST.

56
00:03:31,011 --> 00:03:34,045
I AM HERE TO HELP YOU
WITH YOUR RECOVERY.

57
00:03:34,114 --> 00:03:36,848
UNDERSTAND THAT NO ONE
CAN STOP YOU FROM USING BUT YOU.

58
00:03:36,917 --> 00:03:38,784
[ Muffled Laugh ]
<i>CHECK HIS BAG.</i>

59
00:03:40,119 --> 00:03:43,621
NOW, MR. JONES,
I NEED YOU TO SIGN THIS.

60
00:03:43,690 --> 00:03:47,225
[ Panting ]
WHAT IS IT?

61
00:03:47,294 --> 00:03:51,429
IT IS A CONSENT FORM
EMPOWERING US TO
PLACE YOU IN LOCKDOWN.

62
00:03:51,498 --> 00:03:55,333
LOCKDOWN? I DON'T LIKE
BEING LOCKED UP.

63
00:03:55,402 --> 00:03:58,803
<i> WE NEED TO TAKE CONTROL</i>
<i> DURING THE INITIAL PERIOD</i>
<i> OF YOUR WITHDRAWAL.</i>

64
00:03:58,872 --> 00:04:02,807
I KNOW THAT MAY SOUND EXTREME,
BUT I BELIEVE OUR SUCCESS RATE
SPEAKS FOR ITSELF.

65
00:04:02,876 --> 00:04:05,610
THANK YOU.
WHAT DO YOU GOT, GARRETT?

66
00:04:05,679 --> 00:04:08,813
<i>GOT A CHANGE OF CLOTHES,</i>
<i>BATH ROBE, WALLET,</i>

67
00:04:08,882 --> 00:04:10,882
<i>$48 CASH,</i>
<i>MM-HMM.</i>

68
00:04:10,950 --> 00:04:12,550
RED NOTEBOOK, BLANK.

69
00:04:12,619 --> 00:04:14,720
I KEEP A JOURNAL.
<i>[ Dr. Earl ]</i>
<i>EXCELLENT.</i>

70
00:04:14,788 --> 00:04:17,121
<i>A BIG PART OF YOUR RECOVERY</i>
<i>WILL BE WRITING DOWN...</i>

71
00:04:17,191 --> 00:04:19,123
A SEARCHING AND FEARLESS
MORAL SELF-INVENTORY.

72
00:04:19,193 --> 00:04:21,592
<i>WHOA, WHOA, WHOA.</i>
<i>HOLD ON, HOLD ON.</i>

73
00:04:21,661 --> 00:04:24,028
[ Grunting ]

74
00:04:26,867 --> 00:04:29,333
WE HAVE A CODE OF ETHICS
AROUND HERE.

75
00:04:29,402 --> 00:04:31,836
IT'S CALLED
THE CIRCLE OF TRUST.

76
00:04:31,905 --> 00:04:36,008
YOU GAIN OUR TRUST,
IT COMES BACK TO YOU
IN THE WAY OF PRIVILEGES.

77
00:04:36,076 --> 00:04:40,812
BETRAY THAT TRUST,
THE CIRCLE IS BROKEN.

78
00:04:42,849 --> 00:04:46,451
<i> CONSIDER THIS A WARNING.</i>

79
00:04:46,520 --> 00:04:49,254
[ Straining, Grunting ]

80
00:04:49,323 --> 00:04:51,256
I-I DON'T FEEL SO GOOD.

81
00:04:51,325 --> 00:04:53,124
GET HIM A BUCKET.

82
00:04:56,763 --> 00:04:59,564
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>
<i>"I'M SEARCHING</i>
<i> FOR A SPECIAL MAN.</i>

83
00:04:59,633 --> 00:05:02,768
<i> "IF YOU ARE HANDSOME,</i>
<i> EMOTIONALLY SECURE...</i>

84
00:05:02,836 --> 00:05:05,236
"AND HAVE LEARNED SOME OF
LIFE'S HARDER LESSONS,

85
00:05:05,305 --> 00:05:07,872
WE MIGHT HAVE
SOMETHING IN COMMON."

86
00:05:09,509 --> 00:05:11,809
HOW DOES IT FEEL TO BE
THE MAYOR OF LOSERVILLE?

87
00:05:11,878 --> 00:05:15,380
- I-I READ THAT
FOR ENTERTAINMENT.
- RIGHT.

88
00:05:15,448 --> 00:05:19,350
<i> WHAT DID YOU FIND OUT</i>
<i> ABOUT JAROD'S LATEST CLUE?</i>

89
00:05:19,419 --> 00:05:24,189
<i>THE "101776" CLEARLY RELATES</i>
<i>TO OCTOBER 17, 1976.</i>

90
00:05:24,258 --> 00:05:27,892
<i>THE A-22 PART</i>
<i>HAS ME STUMPED, THOUGH.</i>
<i>IT'S EITHER AUGUST OR APRIL 22,</i>

91
00:05:27,961 --> 00:05:29,794
AND IT COULD RELATE
TO SL 22.

92
00:05:29,863 --> 00:05:33,198
MAYBE IF YOU STOPPED
READING THE WANT ADS AND--
I'LL BE DAMMED.

93
00:05:33,266 --> 00:05:36,134
- WHAT? WHAT IS IT?
- MY LUCKY DAY, APPARENTLY.

94
00:05:36,202 --> 00:05:39,304
"A-22."
SECTION "A," PAGE 22.

95
00:05:39,373 --> 00:05:41,773
BROOTS, GO GET THE MICROFICHE
FROM THE BLUE COVE PAPER...

96
00:05:41,842 --> 00:05:44,108
DATED OCTOBER 17, 1976.

97
00:05:44,177 --> 00:05:47,345
MAYBE WE CAN FIND OUT WHY
JAROD IS HOPPED UP ON HEROIN.

98
00:05:48,749 --> 00:05:51,550
SYDNEY, YOU ALL RIGHT?

99
00:05:51,618 --> 00:05:54,486
<i>[ Jarod ] OKAY, I'M CURED.</i>
<i>LET ME OUT OF HERE.</i>
<i>[ Man ] THIS IS HOW IT PLAYS.</i>

100
00:05:54,554 --> 00:05:57,588
THE DOCTORS ARE LIKE
THE GENERALS. THEY'RE SITTIN'
UP THERE ON THE HILL.

101
00:05:57,657 --> 00:06:00,959
THEY'RE WATCHIN' THE BATTLE.
BUT I'M THE GRUNT.
I'M DOWN THERE IN THE FIELD.

102
00:06:01,027 --> 00:06:03,561
I'M LOOKIN' OUT FOR MY BUDDIES.
YOU GONNA BE
MY BUDDY THERE, JAROD?

103
00:06:03,630 --> 00:06:06,063
SURE. WHY NOT?
GOOD ANSWER.

104
00:06:06,133 --> 00:06:09,000
OKAY, I BRING YOU YOUR MEALS,
I SUPERVISE YOUR DRUG TESTS.

105
00:06:09,069 --> 00:06:12,270
I CLEAN YOUR CLOTHES.
I WILL EVEN MOP UP
YOUR PUKE, MAN.

106
00:06:12,338 --> 00:06:14,706
<i>THE ONLY THING I ASK IN RETURN</i>
<i>IS THAT YOU DON'T GIVE ME</i>
<i>ANY TROUBLE.</i>

107
00:06:14,774 --> 00:06:17,909
THIS AIN'T EASY WHAT YOU'RE
GONNA BE GOIN' THROUGH HERE,
BUT I CAN HELP MAKE IT...

108
00:06:17,978 --> 00:06:20,111
A WHOLE LOT MORE PRODUCTIVE,
OKAY?

109
00:06:20,180 --> 00:06:23,548
- SORRY, BABY. WHOA.
- RUSTY!

110
00:06:23,617 --> 00:06:28,019
HEY, HEY, HEY, HEY, HEY!
COME ON! I'M SICK!

111
00:06:28,087 --> 00:06:30,021
I NEED SOMETHIN'!
<i>SEE THAT GUY?</i>

112
00:06:30,090 --> 00:06:33,959
HE IS NOT MY BUDDY.
COME ON. WE GOTTA
MAKE A PIT STOP.

113
00:06:37,263 --> 00:06:41,066
ALL RIGHT, HERE.
FILL IT UP, UNLEADED.

114
00:06:41,134 --> 00:06:44,302
<i> CAN I GET SOME PRIVACY?</i>
YOU'RE HOLDIN' THE CUP,
AREN'T YA?

115
00:06:44,371 --> 00:06:47,205
[ Buzzer Sounds ]

116
00:06:47,274 --> 00:06:49,407
WELL, NOT EXACTLY
THE FOUR SEASONS.

117
00:06:49,476 --> 00:06:52,510
BUT LET'S FACE IT.
YOU COULDN'T AFFORD
THE FOUR SEASONS.

118
00:06:54,481 --> 00:06:56,514
[ Buzzer Sounds ]

119
00:07:01,121 --> 00:07:04,189
<i> [ Shivering ]</i>
<i> IT'S-IT'S SO COLD IN HERE.</i>

120
00:07:04,257 --> 00:07:06,491
YEAH, WELL, YOU WON'T THINK SO
ONCE THE HOT FLASHES KICK IN.

121
00:07:06,559 --> 00:07:10,395
ALL RIGHT, YOU GOT A BUCKET
FOR WHATEVER COMES UP,
AND IT'LL COME UP. TRUST ME.

122
00:07:10,463 --> 00:07:13,631
I DON'T THINK I CAN DO THIS.
I JUST, UH, NEED
A LITTLE SOMETHIN',

123
00:07:13,700 --> 00:07:15,833
YOU KNOW,
TO CARRY ME THROUGH,
YOU UNDERSTAND?

124
00:07:15,902 --> 00:07:17,902
JUST-JUST SOMETHIN'
FOR TONIGHT, PLEASE?

125
00:07:17,971 --> 00:07:20,571
- GET YOUR HANDS OFF ME, MAN!
- COME ON.
DON'T LEAVE ME IN HERE!

126
00:07:20,640 --> 00:07:23,974
YOU CAN'T LEAVE ME IN HERE!
DON'T LEAVE ME-- COME ON!
DON'T LEAVE ME--

127
00:07:24,043 --> 00:07:26,978
[ Panting, Grunting ]

128
00:07:41,895 --> 00:07:45,096
WELL, BOTTOMS UP.

129
00:07:52,271 --> 00:07:54,705
[ Chattering ]
<i> [ Jarod Vomiting ]</i>

130
00:07:54,775 --> 00:07:56,908
GREAT.

131
00:07:58,712 --> 00:08:01,345
<i> [ Vomiting Continues ]</i>

132
00:08:42,422 --> 00:08:44,355
<i>[ Dr. Earl ]</i>
<i>WE HAVE A NEW MEMBER</i>
<i>OF OUR GROUP.</i>

133
00:08:44,424 --> 00:08:48,393
THIS IS JAROD.
WELCOME TO
HEROIN HILTON, JAROD.

134
00:08:48,462 --> 00:08:52,397
<i>THANK YOU, HUEY. JAROD,</i>
<i>WHY DON'T YOU TELL THE GROUP</i>
<i>WHAT BROUGHT YOU HERE?</i>

135
00:08:52,466 --> 00:08:55,032
<i> A LARGE COP</i>
<i> WITH BAD BREATH.</i>

136
00:08:55,101 --> 00:08:58,135
VERY CLEVER.
PERHAPS YOU COULD BE
A LITTLE MORE SPECIFIC?

137
00:08:58,204 --> 00:09:01,339
<i> NO, MAN, THERE'S NOTHIN'</i>
<i> YOU CAN TELL US WE HAVEN'T</i>
<i> ALREADY HEARD OR SEEN.</i>

138
00:09:02,910 --> 00:09:07,612
LET'S JUST SAY THAT
I'M GOING THROUGH
A SLIGHT IDENTITY CRISIS.

139
00:09:07,681 --> 00:09:10,215
OKAY.

140
00:09:11,652 --> 00:09:15,520
TODAY, I WANT TO TALK
ABOUT RESPONSIBILITY,

141
00:09:15,589 --> 00:09:20,225
<i>ABOUT HOW WE REFUSE</i>
<i>TO TAKE RESPONSIBILITY</i>
<i>FOR OUR ADDICTION.</i>

142
00:09:20,294 --> 00:09:24,729
<i>INSTEAD, WE BLAME</i>
<i>EVERYBODY AND EVERYTHING ELSE.</i>

143
00:09:24,798 --> 00:09:28,633
WELL, I'LL TELL YA THIS, DOC.
YOU KNOW, IF I FALL BACK
INTO MY HABIT,

144
00:09:28,701 --> 00:09:30,435
I'M BLAMING JILL.

145
00:09:30,504 --> 00:09:32,603
SHUT UP, HUEY.
<i>CHICK'S DRIVIN' ME NUTS,</i>

146
00:09:32,672 --> 00:09:35,206
CRYIN' EVERY FIVE SECONDS,

147
00:09:35,274 --> 00:09:37,541
<i>YAMMERIN' ON ABOUT</i>
<i>HER SMACK BINGE LAST WEEK.</i>

148
00:09:37,610 --> 00:09:40,311
"I'M CLEAN. I DIDN'T USE.
I DON'T KNOW HOW IT HAPPENED!"

149
00:09:40,380 --> 00:09:43,748
IT'S THE TRUTH.
I DON'T KNOW
HOW IT HAPPENED.

150
00:09:43,817 --> 00:09:47,552
- THAT'S WHACK, BABY.
- I THOUGHT THIS WAS SUPPOSED
TO BE A SUPPORT GROUP?

151
00:09:47,620 --> 00:09:50,221
SHE TESTED POSITIVE
FOR OPIATES, DUDE.

152
00:09:50,290 --> 00:09:53,090
<i> HER DENYIN' SHE EVEN USED</i>
<i> IS A LIE. YOU'RE A LIAR.</i>

153
00:09:53,159 --> 00:09:55,926
- I'M NOT A LIAR.
- LIAR, LIAR, LIAR.

154
00:09:55,995 --> 00:09:58,363
- YOU DON'T KNOW THAT.
- OKAY, NEW MEAT.

155
00:09:58,431 --> 00:10:01,399
MAYBE THE SMACK
JUST KIND OF FLOATED DOWN
FROM THE HEAVENS...

156
00:10:01,467 --> 00:10:03,301
AND LANDED RIGHT
IN YOUR BLOODSTREAM.

157
00:10:03,369 --> 00:10:05,836
I LOST CUSTODY
OF MY SON LAST WEEK!

158
00:10:05,906 --> 00:10:08,806
<i> WHY WOULD I JEOPARDIZE</i>
<i> THE MOST IMPORTANT THING</i>
<i> IN MY LIFE TO USE?</i>

159
00:10:08,875 --> 00:10:11,576
- BECAUSE YOU'RE A JUNKIE.
- I'M NOT A JUNKIE
ANYMORE, HUEY.

160
00:10:13,346 --> 00:10:16,647
I DON'T WANT HIM SEEIN' ME
IN HERE LIKE THIS.

161
00:10:16,716 --> 00:10:20,251
<i>HAVE AN ATTITUDE</i>
<i>OF GRATITUDE, JILL, HMM?</i>

162
00:10:20,320 --> 00:10:22,187
YOU'RE BLESSED.

163
00:10:22,255 --> 00:10:26,323
YOUR SON IS GOING
TO GET TO SEE YOU AGAIN,
CLEAN AND ALIVE.

164
00:10:26,392 --> 00:10:28,325
WHAT HUEY IS SAYING IS THAT...

165
00:10:28,395 --> 00:10:31,129
YOU NEED TO ACCEPT THE FACT THAT
YOU HAVE A PROBLEM.

166
00:10:31,198 --> 00:10:35,366
I KNOW I HAVE A PROBLEM,
DR. EARL.
I LOST MY SON.

167
00:10:40,506 --> 00:10:43,608
<i> SECTION "A," PAGE 22</i>
<i> HAD FIVE OBITUARIES.</i>

168
00:10:43,677 --> 00:10:45,876
SO I RAN THE NAMES
THROUGH THE DATABASE,
AND ONE OF THEM,

169
00:10:45,945 --> 00:10:48,680
<i> A GUY NAMED DAVID ARNOLD,</i>
<i> USED TO WORK HERE.</i>

170
00:10:48,749 --> 00:10:50,681
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>
<i>WHEN?</i>
<i> IT DOESN'T SAY.</i>

171
00:10:50,751 --> 00:10:53,218
<i> AND THERE'S NO OTHER</i>
<i> INFORMATION ON HIM,</i>
<i> WHICH IS REALLY STRANGE,</i>

172
00:10:53,286 --> 00:10:55,653
BECAUSE YOU KNOW
HOW THIS PLACE IS
ABOUT BACKGROUND CHECKS.

173
00:10:55,722 --> 00:10:59,790
WHICH MAKES YOUR PRESENCE HERE
EVEN MORE OF A MYSTERY.

174
00:10:59,859 --> 00:11:02,293
THIS IS RIDICULOUS!
WHAT IF SOMETHING
HAPPENS TO JAROD...

175
00:11:02,361 --> 00:11:04,995
WHILE WE'RE CHASING GHOSTS?

176
00:11:11,938 --> 00:11:16,307
BROOTS, KEEP WORKING
THE NUMBER CODES, AND STAY
ON THIS DAVID ARNOLD LEAD.

177
00:11:16,376 --> 00:11:18,309
SURE. NO PROBLEM.

178
00:11:18,378 --> 00:11:20,378
AND, BROOTS?

179
00:11:20,446 --> 00:11:22,680
<i> YOU REPORT ONLY TO ME.</i>

180
00:11:37,597 --> 00:11:41,031
THAT'S A FINE-LOOKING
LITTLE BOY YOU HAVE THERE.

181
00:11:41,101 --> 00:11:45,436
I NEVER ACTUALLY KNEW MY MOTHER,
BUT I ALWAYS IMAGINED HOW GREAT
OUR RELATIONSHIP WOULD BE.

182
00:11:45,505 --> 00:11:49,340
LOOK-- JAROD, RIGHT?
I APPRECIATE YOU
DEFENDING ME IN HERE,

183
00:11:49,409 --> 00:11:51,342
BUT, PLEASE,
LEAVE ME ALONE, OKAY?

184
00:11:51,411 --> 00:11:54,145
SORRY, I CAN'T DO THAT.

185
00:11:54,214 --> 00:11:58,582
YOU SEE,
THE REASON I'M IN HERE...

186
00:11:58,651 --> 00:12:02,821
IS TO HELP YOU,
AS A FAVOR TO YOUR FATHER.

187
00:12:02,889 --> 00:12:04,856
MY FATHER'S BEEN DEAD
FOR OVER 20 YEARS.

188
00:12:04,924 --> 00:12:07,091
JILL, I KNOW.

189
00:12:07,160 --> 00:12:10,761
<i>JILL? YOUR LITTLE BOY'S HERE.</i>
<i>HE'S WAITIN' FOR YOU</i>
<i>IN THE VISITATION LOUNGE.</i>

190
00:12:10,830 --> 00:12:13,764
I CAN'T LET HIM
SEE ME LIKE THIS.
YOU'RE HIS MOTHER.

191
00:12:13,833 --> 00:12:17,969
NOTHING CAN CHANGE THE WAY
HE FEELS ABOUT YOU.

192
00:12:58,912 --> 00:13:01,545
<i>[ Man On Speaker ]</i>
<i>HILARY AND I HAVE A LOT</i>
<i>TO DO WITH YOU TODAY, SPORT.</i>

193
00:13:01,614 --> 00:13:04,482
<i>WE'VE GOTTA PICK UP YOUR TUX</i>
<i>FOR THE WEDDING. I'VE GOTTA</i>
<i>GET THE PLANE TICKETS.</i>

194
00:13:04,550 --> 00:13:08,920
SO YOU JUST SAY HI TO MOMMY,
AND THEN LET'S GET GOING, OKAY?

195
00:13:08,988 --> 00:13:11,956
TODD, HONEY?
THE TUXEDO SHOP
IS OPEN LATE,

196
00:13:12,025 --> 00:13:13,991
AND THE TRAVEL AGENT
CAN MESSENGER YOU THE TICKETS.

197
00:13:14,060 --> 00:13:16,160
PLEASE, DADDY?

198
00:13:16,229 --> 00:13:21,165
CHRIS, YOU SPEND
AS MUCH TIME WITH YOUR MOMMY
AS YOU WANT, OKAY?

199
00:13:21,234 --> 00:13:22,700
OKAY.
<i>OKAY.</i>

200
00:13:22,769 --> 00:13:26,037
GUESS WHO.

201
00:13:26,106 --> 00:13:30,441
- MOMMY!
- HEY! LOOK AT YOU!

202
00:13:30,509 --> 00:13:34,511
I'VE MISSED YOU SO MUCH!
I MISSED YOU TOO.

203
00:13:36,416 --> 00:13:39,284
WHY ARE YOU SHAKING, MOMMY?

204
00:13:39,352 --> 00:13:42,219
- MOMMY'S BEEN SICK, BABY.
-<i> ARE YOU GONNA GET BETTER?</i>

205
00:13:42,288 --> 00:13:44,689
YES. AND GUESS WHAT.

206
00:13:44,758 --> 00:13:49,026
IF DR. EARL SAYS IT'S OKAY,
I CAN COME HOME
IN A COUPLE OF DAYS.

207
00:13:49,095 --> 00:13:51,362
<i> [ Chris ]</i>
<i> DOES THAT MEAN I GET</i>
<i> TO LIVE WITH YOU?</i>

208
00:13:53,233 --> 00:13:55,733
WELL, HONEY, NO.

209
00:13:55,802 --> 00:13:57,802
DON'T YOU LOVE ME ANYMORE?

210
00:13:59,105 --> 00:14:02,707
YES, OF COURSE I DO.
I LOVE YOU WITH ALL MY HEART.

211
00:14:08,582 --> 00:14:10,982
OH, GOD.

212
00:14:15,088 --> 00:14:18,356
<i> GARRETT!</i>
<i> CIRCLE OF TRUST, JAROD.</i>

213
00:14:18,424 --> 00:14:20,691
WHATEVER YOU'RE DOING IN HERE,
YOU JUST BROKE THE CIRCLE.

214
00:14:20,760 --> 00:14:23,093
TAKE HIM BACK TO HIS ROOM.

215
00:14:24,664 --> 00:14:26,230
[ Buzzer Sounds ]

216
00:14:29,001 --> 00:14:31,536
COME ON.

217
00:14:31,605 --> 00:14:33,838
YEAH.

218
00:15:13,980 --> 00:15:16,147
[ Beeps, Buzzer Sounds ]

219
00:15:17,517 --> 00:15:19,650
THESE ARE HIS ORDERS.

220
00:15:46,712 --> 00:15:49,846
[ Beeps, Buzzer Sounds ]

221
00:15:55,254 --> 00:15:57,388
- WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?
- I JUST WANNA TALK TO YOU.

222
00:15:57,456 --> 00:16:00,324
<i>THIS IS THE ONLY PLACE THAT</i>
<i>WE CAN TALK UNMONITORED.</i>
<i>PLEASE TRUST ME.</i>

223
00:16:00,393 --> 00:16:02,960
JUST LEAVE ME ALONE.

224
00:16:04,296 --> 00:16:06,763
I DON'T THINK
HE WOULD HAVE WANTED THAT.

225
00:16:08,067 --> 00:16:09,633
WHERE'D YOU GET THIS?

226
00:16:09,702 --> 00:16:13,970
YOUR FATHER GAVE IT TO ME.
I WAS TAKEN FROM MY FAMILY
WHEN I WAS A BOY.

227
00:16:14,040 --> 00:16:17,507
THAT PHOTOGRAPH WAS
YOUR FATHER'S WAY OF GIVING ME
A FAMILY WHEN I NEEDED ONE.

228
00:16:22,681 --> 00:16:26,082
<i>I REALIZE THAT</i>
<i>ALL THIS SOUNDS CRAZY,</i>
<i>BUT IT'S THE TRUTH.</i>

229
00:16:26,151 --> 00:16:29,019
YOU DON'T BELONG IN HERE.
AND I KNOW...

230
00:16:29,087 --> 00:16:32,356
YOU NEVER WOULD HAVE
DONE ANYTHING TO JEOPARDIZE
THE CUSTODY OF YOUR SON.

231
00:16:38,163 --> 00:16:41,098
YOU KNOW, I REMEMBER
WHEN THIS PICTURE WAS TAKEN.

232
00:16:42,501 --> 00:16:45,802
I WAS A JUNIOR
IN HIGH SCHOOL.

233
00:16:45,871 --> 00:16:48,972
THAT WAS THE YEAR
EVERYTHING WENT CRAZY.

234
00:16:49,041 --> 00:16:54,011
I MET THIS GREAT GUY.
A DEALER.

235
00:16:54,079 --> 00:16:56,179
GOD, I GOT STRUNG OUT
SO FAST.

236
00:16:58,284 --> 00:17:00,550
AND YOUR FATHER GOT YOU CLEAN.

237
00:17:02,187 --> 00:17:06,357
<i> NO GUILT TRIPS.</i>
<i> JUST UNCONDITIONAL LOVE.</i>

238
00:17:08,928 --> 00:17:10,928
THEN HE DIED.

239
00:17:12,431 --> 00:17:14,898
I STAYED CLEAN
THROUGH THE WHOLE THING.

240
00:17:14,967 --> 00:17:19,302
<i>I WAS CLEAN FOR A LONG TIME.</i>
<i>THAT'S WHEN I MET TODD.</i>

241
00:17:19,371 --> 00:17:23,139
WE GOT MARRIED, HAD CHRIS.

242
00:17:23,208 --> 00:17:25,475
IT WAS SUCH A GOOD LIFE.

243
00:17:25,544 --> 00:17:28,078
AND THEN YOU STARTED
USING AGAIN.

244
00:17:28,146 --> 00:17:30,180
YEAH.

245
00:17:33,819 --> 00:17:35,752
I DON'T HAVE AN EXCUSE FOR IT.
I SCREWED UP.

246
00:17:35,821 --> 00:17:38,388
BY THE TIME
I REALIZED WHAT I HAD DONE,

247
00:17:38,457 --> 00:17:40,590
TODD HAD LEFT,
AND HE TOOK CHRIS.

248
00:17:40,659 --> 00:17:43,661
THEN TODD MET HILARY.
I KNEW IF I WAS EVER GONNA
GET MY BOY BACK,

249
00:17:43,729 --> 00:17:46,863
I COULD NEVER USE DRUGS AGAIN.

250
00:17:46,932 --> 00:17:50,500
SO I GOT CLEAN AGAIN.
I GOT MY TEACHING CREDENTIAL.

251
00:17:50,569 --> 00:17:54,571
EVERYTHING WAS FINE.
THE COURT WAS GONNA
GIVE ME CUSTODY.

252
00:17:56,509 --> 00:17:58,909
THEN THE DAY BEFORE
THE FINAL HEARING--

253
00:18:00,479 --> 00:18:04,081
I SWEAR TO GOD
I DON'T REMEMBER USING.

254
00:18:05,817 --> 00:18:08,919
SO I LOST ANY CHANCE
OF GETTING MY LITTLE BOY BACK.

255
00:18:14,393 --> 00:18:16,993
THERE IS ALWAYS A CHANCE.

256
00:18:17,062 --> 00:18:19,630
NOT FOR ME.
ONCE HILARY AND TODD
GET MARRIED,

257
00:18:19,699 --> 00:18:22,099
SHE CAN LEGALLY ADOPT HIM,
AND THEN THAT'S THE END.

258
00:18:26,939 --> 00:18:29,306
<i> TELL ME ABOUT THIS DAY</i>
<i> THAT YOU SAID</i>
<i> YOU DON'T REMEMBER USING.</i>

259
00:18:29,375 --> 00:18:33,443
I REMEMBER THE MORNING.
I WAS CLEAN. I CAME HERE
FOR MY WEEKLY DRUG TEST.

260
00:18:33,512 --> 00:18:36,480
<i>I WOKE UP THREE DAYS LATER</i>
<i>STRUNG OUT IN THE PARK.</i>

261
00:18:36,549 --> 00:18:40,717
<i>I WOULDN'T HAVE</i>
<i>THROWN IT ALL AWAY--</i>
<i>NOT MY LIFE, NOT MY FAMILY.</i>

262
00:18:50,696 --> 00:18:53,364
[ Beeps, Buzzer Sounds ]

263
00:18:53,432 --> 00:18:55,499
HELLO, JILL.
HOW ARE WE FEELING TODAY?

264
00:18:55,568 --> 00:18:57,033
OKAY.
<i> GOOD.</i>

265
00:18:57,102 --> 00:18:59,569
NURSES TELL ME
YOU'VE BEEN HAVING
A LITTLE TROUBLE SLEEPING.

266
00:18:59,638 --> 00:19:01,972
<i> WOULD YOU LIKE</i>
<i> A CLONIDINE PATCH?</i>

267
00:19:02,041 --> 00:19:04,308
YES, PLEASE.

268
00:19:20,426 --> 00:19:22,760
ALL RIGHT.

269
00:19:24,596 --> 00:19:27,564
THERE.
THAT SHOULD HELP YOU RELAX.

270
00:19:27,633 --> 00:19:29,166
THANK YOU.

271
00:19:29,235 --> 00:19:31,935
<i>JILL, I JUST WANNA LET YOU KNOW,</i>
<i>IF ALL GOES WELL,</i>

272
00:19:32,003 --> 00:19:34,170
I THINK I CAN HAVE YOU
OUT OF HERE BY FRIDAY.

273
00:19:34,239 --> 00:19:38,174
- REALLY?
- REALLY. WE JUST WANNA
MAKE SURE THAT YOU'RE READY...

274
00:19:38,243 --> 00:19:40,778
AND THERE AREN'T GONNA BE
ANY SETBACKS, OKAY?
I'M READY. I PROMISE.

275
00:19:40,846 --> 00:19:42,712
GOOD. YOU GET SOME SLEEP,

276
00:19:42,781 --> 00:19:44,714
AND I WILL CHECK IN
ON YOU LATER, OKAY?

277
00:19:44,784 --> 00:19:46,750
OKAY.

278
00:19:46,819 --> 00:19:48,752
<i> [ Beeps, Buzzer Sounds ]</i>

279
00:20:01,200 --> 00:20:03,300
<i>[ Broots ]</i>
<i>THE DELAWARE</i>
<i>CARTOGRAPHER'S OFFICE...</i>

280
00:20:03,369 --> 00:20:08,238
IS E-MAILING ME A MAP
CODED 101776.

281
00:20:08,307 --> 00:20:10,740
- A-22 SHOULD BE THE COORDINATES
THAT LEAD US TO JAROD.
- GOOD WORK.

282
00:20:10,809 --> 00:20:13,410
<i>WILL YOU LET US KNOW</i>
<i>THE MINUTE IT COMES IN?</i>

283
00:20:13,479 --> 00:20:17,714
- OH, YEAH, YEAH.
- BROOTS, I WANNA REVIEW
YOUR G-4 REPORT WITH YOU.

284
00:20:17,783 --> 00:20:20,250
ALL RIGHT. I'LL CATCH UP
WITH YOU, SYDNEY.

285
00:20:20,319 --> 00:20:23,086
HMM.

286
00:20:23,155 --> 00:20:25,956
- WHAT DO YOU GOT?
- OKAY.

287
00:20:26,025 --> 00:20:29,326
YOU KNOW WINKEY, THE OLD GUY
WITH THE FACIAL TICKS THAT
WORKS DOWN IN THE INFIRMARY?

288
00:20:29,394 --> 00:20:31,962
- WE HAVEN'T HAD THE PLEASURE.
- OKAY. ANYWAY,

289
00:20:32,030 --> 00:20:35,332
HE REMEMBERS THIS DAVID ARNOLD
WHO USED TO WORK THERE
AS AN ORDERLY LIKE 20 YEARS AGO.

290
00:20:35,401 --> 00:20:39,002
SO I CROSS-REFERENCED
ARNOLD'S NAME WITH
THE INFIRMARY'S D.S.A. DATABASE,

291
00:20:39,070 --> 00:20:41,405
AND I CAME UP
WITH TWO MATCHES.

292
00:20:41,473 --> 00:20:44,741
THE ONLY PROBLEM
IS THEY'RE MISSING
FROM WINKEY'S ARCHIVES.

293
00:20:44,810 --> 00:20:46,743
SOMEBODY'S REALLY GONE
TO SOME TROUBLE...

294
00:20:46,812 --> 00:20:49,980
ERASING THIS GUY FROM
THE HISTORY BOOKS AROUND HERE.

295
00:20:50,049 --> 00:20:55,619
YOU'VE BEEN MAKING
UNAUTHORIZED ENTRIES INTO
THE INFIRMARY'S DATABASE.

296
00:20:57,323 --> 00:21:00,290
IF IT'S DAVID ARNOLD
YOU WANT TO KNOW ABOUT,

297
00:21:00,359 --> 00:21:05,462
I CAN TELL YOU HE WAS ONE OF
THE KINDEST, GENTLEST MEN I EVER
HAD THE PLEASURE OF KNOWING.

298
00:21:06,699 --> 00:21:10,300
-WHAT'S HE DOING THESE DAYS?
-PUSHING UP DAISIES.

299
00:21:12,070 --> 00:21:14,170
ARNOLD IS DEADER
THAN YOUR HAIR FOLLICLES.

300
00:21:14,239 --> 00:21:17,407
[ Sighs ]

301
00:21:17,476 --> 00:21:19,876
TELL ME THEN, MISS PARKER,

302
00:21:19,945 --> 00:21:24,181
<i>HOW DOES DAVID ARNOLD GET YOU</i>
<i>ANY CLOSER TO FINDING JAROD?</i>

303
00:21:24,249 --> 00:21:29,052
WE EXPLORE ALL AVENUES
IN PURSUIT OF JAROD,
EVEN THE DEAD ONES.

304
00:21:35,126 --> 00:21:37,861
<i> HE WOULDN'T BE BUGGING US</i>
<i> ABOUT A DATABASE HIT...</i>

305
00:21:37,930 --> 00:21:39,863
UNLESS HE HAD SOMETHING TO HIDE.

306
00:21:39,932 --> 00:21:42,966
THE ANSWER LIES
IN THOSE MISSING D.S.A.s,
WHICH ARE MOSTLY LIKELY...

307
00:21:43,035 --> 00:21:45,468
IN RAINES'S
PRIVATE COLLECTION.

308
00:21:50,275 --> 00:21:52,942
<i>♪♪ [ Dance ]</i>
<i>[ Woman ] GREAT. AND ONE,</i>
<i>AND TWO, AND THREE, AND FOUR.</i>

309
00:21:53,011 --> 00:21:56,346
KEEP IT GOING.
ALMOST FINISHED. BREATHE.

310
00:21:56,415 --> 00:22:00,116
GOOD, AND ARMS.
AND ONE, AND TWO,
AND THREE, AND FOUR.

311
00:22:00,185 --> 00:22:02,118
GOOD JOB.

312
00:22:03,989 --> 00:22:08,158
HEY, NICE RIDE, DUDE.
WHAT ARE WE WAITIN' FOR?
LET'S GET THE HELL OUT OF HERE.

313
00:22:08,226 --> 00:22:11,261
EVEN IF I COULD START IT,
THEY DON'T LET ME RIDE IT.

314
00:22:11,330 --> 00:22:13,263
YOU KNOW ANYTHING
ABOUT MOTORCYCLE MAINTENANCE?

315
00:22:13,331 --> 00:22:15,732
WELL, I READ A BOOK
ON IT ONCE.

316
00:22:15,801 --> 00:22:17,934
NOTHIN' TO DO WITH MOTORCYCLES,
HOWEVER.

317
00:22:18,003 --> 00:22:22,171
WHOA, WHOA. WHOA. GOD.
DOES IT FLOOD WHEN
YOU HIT THE THROTTLE?

318
00:22:22,240 --> 00:22:24,541
YEAH.

319
00:22:24,610 --> 00:22:28,044
THE TABS FROM YOUR FLOAT BOWL
ARE DISCONNECTED
FROM THE NEEDLE, SEE?

320
00:22:29,815 --> 00:22:32,382
I'LL BE DAMMED.
HEY, THANKS.

321
00:22:32,451 --> 00:22:34,951
COOL SHIRT.
WHAT'S "SKINT RABBIT"?

322
00:22:35,020 --> 00:22:36,953
<i> IT'S A ROCK-AND-ROLL BAND.</i>

323
00:22:37,022 --> 00:22:39,789
<i>WE HAD A BIG HIT</i>
<i>IN THE '80s.</i>

324
00:22:39,858 --> 00:22:43,093
- "BLOODY LOVE BONES"?
- I WAS KINDA OUT OF IT
IN THE '80s.

325
00:22:43,162 --> 00:22:46,863
AND THE '70s.
MOST OF THE '90s,
FOR THAT MATTER.

326
00:22:46,931 --> 00:22:49,032
YEAH, WHO WASN'T?
BUT I WAS THEIR HEAD ROADIE.

327
00:22:49,101 --> 00:22:53,736
<i>WE WENT EVERYWHERE.</i>
<i>TOURED WITH THE BIGGEST.</i>
<i>STONES, ALLMAN BROTHERS.</i>

328
00:22:53,805 --> 00:22:55,839
THEN WE RELEASED
TWO LAME ALBUMS.

329
00:22:55,908 --> 00:22:58,908
THE NEXT THING YOU KNOW,
WE ARE WARMIN' UP
HIGH SCHOOL GYMS FOR AIR SUPPLY.

330
00:23:00,679 --> 00:23:02,879
WERE THEY HAVING TROUBLE
WITH THEIR VENTILATION SYSTEM?

331
00:23:05,217 --> 00:23:06,950
EXACTLY.

332
00:23:09,354 --> 00:23:13,890
HEY, LISTEN, BROTHER, UM,
I REALLY NEED TO SCORE.

333
00:23:13,959 --> 00:23:16,092
I DON'T KNOW WHAT
YOU'RE TALKIN' ABOUT.

334
00:23:16,161 --> 00:23:19,162
COME ON. YOUR CLAMMY SKIN,
YOUR BEADY LITTLE PUPILS.

335
00:23:19,230 --> 00:23:22,665
I THINK YOU KNOW
EXACTLY WHAT I MEAN.
COME ON.

336
00:23:24,169 --> 00:23:26,670
HELP ME OUT.

337
00:23:28,207 --> 00:23:30,774
GARRETT'S YOUR MAN.

338
00:23:30,842 --> 00:23:32,843
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>
<i>GARRETT?</i>

339
00:23:32,911 --> 00:23:35,178
UNLESS HE GOT BUSTED AGAIN.
AGAIN?

340
00:23:35,247 --> 00:23:39,082
EARL NAILED HIM
A FEW WEEKS AGO DEALIN'
SMACK TO AN OUTPATIENT.

341
00:23:39,150 --> 00:23:43,453
HOW DOES AN ORDERLY IN
A DRUG REHABILITATION CENTER
GET AWAY WITH THAT?

342
00:23:43,522 --> 00:23:47,356
<i>HEY, MAN, THERE'S STUFF</i>
<i>GOIN' ON AROUND HERE</i>
<i>NONE OF US WILL EVER KNOW ABOUT.</i>

343
00:23:56,802 --> 00:23:58,802
JILL?

344
00:24:01,172 --> 00:24:03,106
JILL? JILL?

345
00:24:04,343 --> 00:24:06,643
JILL?

346
00:24:11,216 --> 00:24:15,051
SOMEBODY GET IN HERE!
SHE'S O.D.'ING! JILL?

347
00:24:15,120 --> 00:24:17,888
I WILL TAKE CARE OF THIS.
I WILL TAKE CARE OF THIS.
CHECK HER RESPIRATION.

348
00:24:17,956 --> 00:24:20,223
<i> I NEED AN AIRWAY</i>
<i> AND SOME O-2 STAT!</i>

349
00:24:20,292 --> 00:24:23,026
GET IN HERE! GET IN THERE!
GET IN THERE!

350
00:24:24,730 --> 00:24:26,963
<i> JILL? JILL?</i>

351
00:24:27,032 --> 00:24:28,965
JILL, HOW COULD YOU
DO THIS TO YOURSELF?

352
00:24:34,006 --> 00:24:36,472
<i>[ Broots ]</i>
<i>RAINES ALMOST CAUGHT ME.</i>

353
00:24:36,541 --> 00:24:41,278
I HAD TO HIDE UNDER HIS COUCH
FOR OVER AN HOUR.

354
00:24:41,346 --> 00:24:44,047
THEN HIS MASSEUSE CAME IN
AND RUBBED HIM DOWN WITH OIL...

355
00:24:44,116 --> 00:24:46,516
WHILE THEY WERE SINGING
"SHALL WE GATHER AT THE RIVER."

356
00:24:46,584 --> 00:24:49,486
THE D.S.A.s?

357
00:24:49,555 --> 00:24:52,255
YOU ARE NOT GONNA BELIEVE THIS.

358
00:25:03,935 --> 00:25:05,935
[ Buzzer Sounds ]

359
00:25:07,639 --> 00:25:11,007
<i>JILL.</i>
JAROD, I SWEAR I DON'T KNOW
HOW THIS HAPPENED.

360
00:25:11,076 --> 00:25:14,677
<i>IT DOESN'T MATTER.</i>
<i>WHAT MATTERS NOW</i>
<i>IS GETTING YOU THROUGH THIS.</i>

361
00:25:14,746 --> 00:25:17,280
COME ON, COME ON.
LET'S GET YOU IN THE BED.
COME ON. COME ON.

362
00:25:17,349 --> 00:25:20,283
I'M BEGINNING TO THINK MAYBE
I'M DOING THIS.

363
00:25:20,352 --> 00:25:24,054
I CAN'T REMEMBER
WHAT'S HAPPENING TO ME ANYMORE.
OH, GOD.

364
00:25:24,123 --> 00:25:27,057
I CAN'T GO THROUGH THIS AGAIN.
I DON'T HAVE THE STRENGTH.

365
00:25:27,126 --> 00:25:29,493
YOU'RE GOING TO HAVE
TO FIND THE STRENGTH
FOR YOUR SON.

366
00:25:29,561 --> 00:25:31,728
- I'VE LOST HIM.
- NO, YOU HAVEN'T.

367
00:25:31,797 --> 00:25:34,397
[ Sobbing ]

368
00:25:35,534 --> 00:25:37,467
[ Vomiting ]

369
00:25:43,608 --> 00:25:45,741
WHY ARE YOU DOING THIS?

370
00:25:45,810 --> 00:25:49,078
- I OWE YOUR FATHER.
- FOR WHAT?

371
00:25:50,516 --> 00:25:52,482
<i>[ Young Jarod ]</i>
<i>SOMEBODY HELP ME!</i>

372
00:25:52,550 --> 00:25:54,918
SOMEBODY HELP ME!

373
00:25:54,986 --> 00:25:58,855
[ Grunting, Sobbing ]

374
00:25:58,923 --> 00:26:02,492
SOMEBODY HELP ME!
[ Sobbing Continues ]

375
00:26:02,561 --> 00:26:06,596
- SO HE HAD A BAD FLU.
- THIS ISN'T THE FLU,
MISS PARKER. WATCH.

376
00:26:06,665 --> 00:26:08,198
<i>[ Tape Rewinding ]</i>

377
00:26:35,127 --> 00:26:38,761
<i>THE SELF-RIGHTEOUS</i>
<i>SON OF A BITCH</i>
<i>GOT JAROD HOOKED ON NARCOTICS.</i>

378
00:26:44,102 --> 00:26:46,702
HERE.

379
00:26:46,771 --> 00:26:49,205
YOU HAVE TO DRINK
AND STAY HYDRATED.

380
00:26:51,810 --> 00:26:54,010
ONE MORE. COME ON.
NO.

381
00:26:57,882 --> 00:27:01,584
WHY WOULD THAT PLACE--
WHY WOULD THE CENTRE
GIVE A CHILD DRUGS?

382
00:27:01,653 --> 00:27:04,053
BECAUSE TO THEM,
I WAS NEVER A CHILD.

383
00:27:07,459 --> 00:27:09,325
YOU CALLED FOR ME, DOCTOR?

384
00:27:11,129 --> 00:27:15,699
I NEED YOU
TO CLEAN UP THE ROOM.
THE BOY'S SICK.

385
00:27:17,903 --> 00:27:20,169
YES, SIR.

386
00:27:20,238 --> 00:27:22,271
HEY, KID.
I'M ONE OF THE ORDERLIES.

387
00:27:22,340 --> 00:27:25,441
HELP ME, PLEASE.

388
00:27:25,510 --> 00:27:28,111
WHAT'S WRONG WITH YOU?

389
00:27:30,415 --> 00:27:32,782
OH, MY GOD.
WHO DID THIS TO YOU?

390
00:27:32,850 --> 00:27:35,752
<i>PLEASE HELP ME.</i>

391
00:27:35,821 --> 00:27:37,787
JUST HANG IN THERE, BUDDY.

392
00:27:37,856 --> 00:27:40,323
I'M GONNA HELP YOU
THROUGH THIS, OKAY?
EVERYTHING'S GONNA BE FINE.

393
00:27:40,392 --> 00:27:42,325
<i>[ Broots ]</i>
<i>THAT'S DAVID ARNOLD.</i>

394
00:27:42,394 --> 00:27:46,797
THERE'S THE CONNECTION
TO JAROD. ARNOLD HELPED HIM
GET THROUGH DETOX.

395
00:27:46,865 --> 00:27:49,966
<i>I'M SO HOT,</i>
<i>I FEEL LIKE I'M BURNING UP.</i>

396
00:27:50,034 --> 00:27:53,769
- JUST HANG TOUGH. IT'LL PASS.
-<i> I HURT ALL OVER.</i>

397
00:27:53,838 --> 00:27:58,541
HANG TOUGH. IT'LL PASS.
[ Vomits ]

398
00:27:58,610 --> 00:28:00,643
I DON'T THINK
I CAN DO THIS.
YES, YOU CAN.

399
00:28:00,712 --> 00:28:03,847
JUST STAY FOCUSED ON ME.
COME ON. COME ON.

400
00:28:03,916 --> 00:28:06,349
JUST A LITTLE BIT TO MAKE
THE PAIN GO AWAY.

401
00:28:06,418 --> 00:28:10,086
I CAN'T DO THAT, JAROD.
I CAN'T DO THIS!

402
00:28:11,723 --> 00:28:15,325
YOU'VE GOTTA GET ME SOMETHING.
PLEASE-PLEASE GET ME SOMETHING.

403
00:28:19,164 --> 00:28:21,964
HOW ABOUT HIM?
IS HE ENOUGH?

404
00:28:27,372 --> 00:28:30,006
<i> I NEED MY-MY FAMILY</i>
<i> HERE TO HELP ME.</i>

405
00:28:30,075 --> 00:28:32,442
WHERE IS YOUR FAMILY?

406
00:28:32,510 --> 00:28:36,379
I DON'T KNOW.
I CAN'T REMEMBER.

407
00:28:42,787 --> 00:28:45,855
HERE. YOU HANG ONTO THAT.

408
00:28:45,924 --> 00:28:49,225
<i>LET MY DAUGHTER JILL AND I</i>
<i>BE YOUR FAMILY.</i>

409
00:28:49,294 --> 00:28:52,662
I DON'T KNOW HOW
I'M EVER GONNA REPAY YOU
FOR THIS.

410
00:28:52,730 --> 00:28:55,799
DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.

411
00:28:55,867 --> 00:28:57,967
ONE DAY, YOU WILL.

412
00:29:03,808 --> 00:29:07,877
WAIT. MISS PARKER,
YOU HAVE TO SEE THE NEXT D.S.A.

413
00:29:11,250 --> 00:29:13,617
MR. ARNOLD?
YES, SIR?

414
00:29:13,685 --> 00:29:15,785
YOU'RE TO BE COMMENDED.

415
00:29:15,854 --> 00:29:17,854
THANK YOU.

416
00:29:19,358 --> 00:29:21,324
I DON'T MEAN TO OVERSTEP
MY POSITION HERE,

417
00:29:21,393 --> 00:29:25,729
BUT WHAT POSSIBLE REASON
COULD YOU HAVE TO GET
THIS KID HOOKED ON DRUGS?

418
00:29:25,797 --> 00:29:28,298
THAT'S NOT YOUR CONCERN.

419
00:29:28,367 --> 00:29:32,235
OH. I'M MAKING IT
MY CONCERN, SIR.

420
00:29:33,372 --> 00:29:36,406
YOU'LL BE AMPLY REWARDED
FOR YOUR EFFORTS.

421
00:29:38,477 --> 00:29:40,409
YOU KNOW,
YOU CAN KEEP YOUR MONEY.

422
00:29:40,478 --> 00:29:43,880
I DON'T WANT ANYTHING
TO DO WITH THIS PLACE.

423
00:29:55,994 --> 00:29:58,795
WE HAVE A PROBLEM.

424
00:29:58,864 --> 00:30:00,763
<i>[ Broots ]</i>
<i>THIS IS DATED OCTOBER 17,</i>

425
00:30:00,832 --> 00:30:03,867
THE DAY BEFORE DAVID ARNOLD...

426
00:30:03,936 --> 00:30:07,136
ACCIDENTALLY DROWNED
IN HIS OWN SWIMMING POOL.

427
00:30:07,205 --> 00:30:09,439
RAINES HAD HIM KILLED
TO KEEP HIM QUIET.

428
00:30:11,342 --> 00:30:14,077
I CAN'T HELP WONDERING,
WHERE WAS SYDNEY
DURING ALL THIS?

429
00:30:14,146 --> 00:30:17,814
<i>HE WAS JAROD'S PROTECTOR.</i>
<i>HOW COULD HE LET THIS HAPPEN?</i>

430
00:30:19,084 --> 00:30:22,319
THAT'S A GOOD QUESTION.

431
00:30:22,387 --> 00:30:26,889
I DESERVE TO LOSE HIM.
HILARY WILL MAKE
A MUCH BETTER MOTHER.

432
00:30:29,594 --> 00:30:32,295
I JUST DON'T KNOW
HOW THIS HAPPENED.

433
00:30:46,645 --> 00:30:49,245
WELL, IT'S ABOUT TIME
WE FOUND OUT.

434
00:32:16,501 --> 00:32:18,601
GARRETT, YOU GOT
A PATIENT LOOSE.

435
00:32:20,205 --> 00:32:22,738
[ Beeps, Buzzer Sounds ]

436
00:32:25,911 --> 00:32:27,910
WHAT THE HELL WERE YOU DOIN'
OUT OF YOUR ROOM?

437
00:32:27,979 --> 00:32:31,114
WERE YOU AFRAID I WAS GONNA
FIND<i> YOUR</i> DRUG STASH?

438
00:32:31,183 --> 00:32:33,249
ALL RIGHT,
YOU SON OF A BITCH.

439
00:32:40,992 --> 00:32:42,925
HOW COULD YOU DO THAT?

440
00:32:42,995 --> 00:32:45,528
HOW COULD YOU GIVE DRUGS
TO A WOMAN WHO WAS TRYIN'
TO TURN HER LIFE AROUND?

441
00:32:45,597 --> 00:32:49,832
WHAT THE HELL
ARE YOU TALKIN' ABOUT?
I'M TALKING ABOUT JILL ARNOLD!

442
00:32:49,901 --> 00:32:53,302
I'M TALKING ABOUT DOCTORING
HER CLONIDINE PATCH
WITH PURE HEROIN.

443
00:32:53,371 --> 00:32:55,372
I DIDN'T!

444
00:32:58,743 --> 00:33:01,611
YOU WANNA DEAL WITH ME,
OR SHOULD I CALL THE POLICE?
GO TO HELL.

445
00:33:01,680 --> 00:33:04,147
YOU'RE THE DRUG SUPPLIER HERE.
WHY'D YOU DO IT?

446
00:33:04,216 --> 00:33:08,051
I SWEAR! I SWEAR!
I DON'T EVEN HAVE ACCESS
TO THE CLONIDINE PATCHES.

447
00:33:08,119 --> 00:33:12,822
ONLY DR. EARL COULD HAVE
LACED THEM WITH HEROIN.
HEROIN HE GOT FROM YOU!

448
00:33:12,891 --> 00:33:15,357
[ Toilet Flushes ]
ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT,
ALL RIGHT.

449
00:33:15,426 --> 00:33:17,560
WHEN EARL CAUGHT ME
DEALIN' TO HUEY,
HE THREATENED...

450
00:33:17,629 --> 00:33:20,396
TO HAVE ME ARRESTED
UNLESS I SCORED FOR HIM,
ALL RIGHT?

451
00:33:20,465 --> 00:33:22,665
I HAD NO IDEA
HE WAS GONNA USE IT
ON A PATIENT.

452
00:33:22,734 --> 00:33:25,701
WHY IS DR. EARL KEEPING
JILL ARNOLD ON DRUGS?
I DON'T KNOW!

453
00:33:25,770 --> 00:33:28,838
I DON'T KNOW! I DON'T.
I SWEAR TO GOD, I DON'T.

454
00:33:28,906 --> 00:33:31,741
BUT I CAN GET YOU
INTO HIS OFFICE.

455
00:33:56,168 --> 00:33:59,536
[ No Audible Dialogue ]

456
00:34:02,673 --> 00:34:05,175
HELLO, HILARY.
I'M CALLING FOR DR. EARL.

457
00:34:05,243 --> 00:34:08,878
IT SEEMS A SITUATION HAS COME UP
REGARDING JILL ARNOLD.

458
00:34:08,946 --> 00:34:11,080
HE NEEDS YOU TO COME DOWN HERE
RIGHT AWAY.

459
00:34:45,283 --> 00:34:47,784
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>
<i>UH, HILARY, RIGHT?</i>
<i>DR. EARL SAID...</i>

460
00:34:47,852 --> 00:34:49,886
HE WAS RUNNING
JUST A LITTLE BIT LATE.

461
00:34:51,456 --> 00:34:53,422
CAN I OFFER YOU
A GLASS OF WATER WHILE YOU WAIT?

462
00:35:00,965 --> 00:35:03,032
<i>[ Young Jarod Groaning ]</i>

463
00:35:05,303 --> 00:35:08,070
SOMEBODY HELP ME!

464
00:35:08,139 --> 00:35:11,607
<i> SYDNEY, HOW COULD YOU LET</i>
<i> THIS HAPPEN?</i>

465
00:35:11,676 --> 00:35:14,277
HE WAS JUST A BOY, SYD.

466
00:35:14,345 --> 00:35:17,746
IN THOSE DAYS, THE CENTRE
WAS WORKING WITH PEOPLE...

467
00:35:17,816 --> 00:35:21,451
<i>WHO WERE TRYING TO PERFECT</i>
<i>A SYNTHESIZED NARCOTIC...</i>

468
00:35:21,519 --> 00:35:23,652
<i> THAT MIGHT ENHANCE</i>
<i> MENTAL PERFORMANCE.</i>

469
00:35:23,721 --> 00:35:27,289
SO YOU LET THEM
EXPERIMENT ON JAROD?

470
00:35:27,358 --> 00:35:29,792
IT WAS RAINES'S DECISION.

471
00:35:29,861 --> 00:35:35,598
<i> I GUESS THE IDEA OF</i>
<i> A GREAT MIND LIKE JAROD'S</i>
<i> BECOMING GREATER STILL...</i>

472
00:35:35,667 --> 00:35:38,300
<i> WAS JUST TOO EXCITING</i>
<i> TO WALK AWAY FROM.</i>

473
00:35:38,369 --> 00:35:40,502
<i> THE DRUG, OF COURSE,</i>
<i> IT TURNED OUT,</i>

474
00:35:40,571 --> 00:35:42,772
HAD PRETTY SERIOUS
SIDE EFFECTS.

475
00:35:42,841 --> 00:35:46,342
<i> RAPID ADDICTION</i>
<i> AND DEVASTATING WITHDRAWAL.</i>

476
00:35:46,410 --> 00:35:50,346
SO RAINES TURNS JAROD
INTO A JUNKIE LAB RAT,

477
00:35:50,415 --> 00:35:52,047
<i>AND YOU BURY YOUR HEAD</i>
<i>IN THE SAND?</i>

478
00:35:52,116 --> 00:35:54,817
SYDNEY, WHY?

479
00:36:18,542 --> 00:36:21,210
[ Panting, Grunting ]

480
00:36:30,955 --> 00:36:32,989
THEY TURNED SYDNEY
INTO AN ADDICT.

481
00:36:38,930 --> 00:36:41,297
<i> [ Dr. Earl Groaning ]</i>

482
00:36:45,102 --> 00:36:47,102
[ Both Gasp ]

483
00:36:47,171 --> 00:36:49,772
- OH, MY GOD. WHERE AM I?
- WHAT'S HAPPENING TO ME?

484
00:36:49,840 --> 00:36:53,910
I WOULD IMAGINE THAT JILL ARNOLD
MUST HAVE ASKED HERSELF
THE VERY SAME QUESTION.

485
00:36:53,978 --> 00:36:57,713
-JAROD?
-I THINK WE SHOULD HAVE
A LITTLE GROUP THERAPY SESSION.

486
00:36:57,782 --> 00:37:02,284
ONLY THIS TIME,
THE TWO OF YOU
GET TO BE THE PATIENTS.

487
00:37:02,353 --> 00:37:05,021
- WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?
- CIRCLE OF TRUST, DOC.

488
00:37:05,089 --> 00:37:08,190
<i>YOU GIVE JILL ARNOLD DRUGS</i>
<i>AGAINST HER WILL.</i>

489
00:37:08,259 --> 00:37:10,192
I DO THE VERY SAME THING
TO THE TWO OF YOU.

490
00:37:10,261 --> 00:37:12,595
<i>ONLY THIS TIME,</i>
<i>I USE A HYBRID NARCOTIC...</i>

491
00:37:12,664 --> 00:37:16,432
<i>THAT CHEMICALLY TRICKS THE BRAIN</i>
<i>INTO THINKING YOU'VE BEEN</i>
<i>ADDICTED FOR YEARS.</i>

492
00:37:16,501 --> 00:37:20,069
<i>WHAT YOU'RE EXPERIENCING NOW,</i>
<i>PHYSICALLY AND MENTALLY,</i>

493
00:37:20,138 --> 00:37:23,706
THAT'S WHAT'S KNOWN AS
"COLD TURKEY."

494
00:37:23,775 --> 00:37:26,709
- GOBBLE, GOBBLE.
- YOU'RE SICK.
- YOU SON OF A BITCH.

495
00:37:26,777 --> 00:37:30,613
NOW, THAT IS NOT EXPRESSING
AN ATTITUDE OF GRATITUDE, DOC.

496
00:37:30,681 --> 00:37:32,648
<i>BUT NOT TO WORRY.</i>
<i>I BROUGHT ALONG...</i>

497
00:37:32,717 --> 00:37:35,785
SOME CLONIDINE PATCHES
TO HELP TAKE THAT PAIN AWAY.

498
00:37:35,854 --> 00:37:38,054
PLEASE, GIVE ME A PATCH.
FIRST, WE SHOULD TALK ABOUT...

499
00:37:38,123 --> 00:37:40,890
INVESTIGATING OUR MORAL
SELF-INVENTORY TO DECIDE...

500
00:37:40,959 --> 00:37:42,959
WHICH ONE OF YOU ACTUALLY
DESERVES A PATCH.
<i> GIVE IT TO ME!</i>

501
00:37:43,027 --> 00:37:47,496
WHO THE HELL ARE YOU?
I'M SOMEBODY THAT CAN
HELP END YOUR TORMENT.

502
00:37:47,565 --> 00:37:50,165
JUST TELL ME THE TRUTH.
COME ON.
I CAN'T TAKE THIS.

503
00:37:50,234 --> 00:37:54,437
<i>DON'T GIVE IT TO HER, JAROD!</i>
<i>GIVE IT TO ME!</i>
JUST-JUST-JUST TALK TO ME.

504
00:37:54,505 --> 00:37:58,441
I CAN'T.
MMM-- OKAY. OKAY.

505
00:37:58,510 --> 00:38:00,743
PLEASE,
GIVE-GIVE ME A PATCH.

506
00:38:00,812 --> 00:38:03,680
I GUESS YOU CAN LOOK FORWARD
TO THE NEXT EIGHT HOURS...

507
00:38:03,748 --> 00:38:05,748
WITH YOUR HEAD IN A BUCKET.
[ Mimics Vomiting ]

508
00:38:05,816 --> 00:38:08,150
<i> GIVE ME A PATCH, PLEASE.</i>

509
00:38:08,219 --> 00:38:10,853
<i>[ Hilary ]</i>
<i>PLEASE GIVE ME A PATCH.</i>
ONE CLONIDINE PATCH DOWN.

510
00:38:10,922 --> 00:38:13,456
<i> [ Dr. Earl ]</i>
<i> JAROD, GIVE IT TO ME.</i>
OKAY.

511
00:38:13,524 --> 00:38:15,991
<i> OKAY. HE DID IT.</i>

512
00:38:16,060 --> 00:38:17,927
- WHAT?
- HE NEEDED THE MONEY.

513
00:38:17,995 --> 00:38:21,830
-SHUT UP, YOU STUPID BITCH!
-OH, PLEASE. COME ON.
YOU SAID NOBODY WOULD FIND OUT.

514
00:38:21,899 --> 00:38:25,168
YOU'RE THE ONE WHO NEEDED
THAT STUPID KID.
YOU WANTED THE BOY!

515
00:38:25,236 --> 00:38:28,637
- HEY!
- PLEASE, GIVE ME
ONE OF THE PATCHES.

516
00:38:28,706 --> 00:38:30,940
LET ME GUESS.
IT WENT SOMETHING LIKE THIS.

517
00:38:31,009 --> 00:38:34,110
<i> TODD MOFFETT IS</i>
<i> A VERY RICH MAN.</i>

518
00:38:34,178 --> 00:38:36,946
SO RICH, IN FACT,
THAT IF YOU TWO
WERE TO GET DIVORCED,

519
00:38:37,014 --> 00:38:39,147
<i> YOU COULD STAND TO MAKE</i>
<i> ONE HELL OF A PAYDAY,</i>

520
00:38:39,216 --> 00:38:41,784
ESPECIALLY IF YOU WERE
TO ADOPT HIS SON.

521
00:38:41,853 --> 00:38:44,620
<i> AND WHAT BETTER WAY</i>
<i> TO INSURE CUSTODY...</i>

522
00:38:44,689 --> 00:38:47,623
THAN TO TURN
HIS BIOLOGICAL MOTHER
INTO A JUNKIE.

523
00:38:47,692 --> 00:38:53,296
-AND WHO BETTER TO HELP YOU THAN
YOUR EX-COLLEGE SWEETHEART.
-HOW DID YOU KNOW THAT?

524
00:38:53,364 --> 00:38:55,665
LET'S JUST SAY THAT
I TOOK A LITTLE PEEK...

525
00:38:55,734 --> 00:38:58,134
INTO THE DOC'S
COLLEGE YEARBOOK.

526
00:38:58,203 --> 00:39:01,571
YOU TWO MAKE
SUCH A CUTE LITTLE COUPLE.
IT SEEMS SO SAD...

527
00:39:01,639 --> 00:39:03,906
THAT COLLEGE SWEETHEARTS
SUCH AS YOURSELF...

528
00:39:03,975 --> 00:39:06,842
ARE GONNA HAVE TO EXPERIENCE
SUCH HORRIFIC PAIN.

529
00:39:06,911 --> 00:39:12,214
<i>I'VE HAD MY EXPERIENCE WITH</i>
<i>THAT LITTLE DEVIL YOU'RE ON.</i>
<i>AND LET ME TELL YOU--</i>

530
00:39:12,283 --> 00:39:15,051
SOMEBODY HELP ME!

531
00:39:15,119 --> 00:39:17,586
IT'S A BITCH.

532
00:39:19,324 --> 00:39:21,890
<i> ONLY ONE</i>
<i> CLONIDINE PATCH LEFT.</i>

533
00:39:21,959 --> 00:39:26,162
<i>IT WOULD BE A SHAME TO HAVE</i>
<i>TO WHITE-KNUCKLE IT</i>
<i>THROUGH SUCH A TERRIBLE DETOX.</i>

534
00:39:26,230 --> 00:39:28,730
<i> OKAY!</i>
<i> I DID IT.</i>

535
00:39:28,799 --> 00:39:32,001
<i> I DRUGGED JILL ARNOLD</i>
<i> SO SHE WOULD LOSE CUSTODY</i>
<i> OF HER SON.</i>

536
00:39:32,070 --> 00:39:34,937
-<i> NOW CAN I HAVE</i>
<i> THAT PATCH, PLEASE?</i>
- NO, HE DID IT.

537
00:39:35,005 --> 00:39:37,072
<i> PLEASE GIVE ME</i>
<i> THE PATCH.</i>

538
00:39:37,141 --> 00:39:39,208
LIKE YOU SAY, DOC,

539
00:39:39,277 --> 00:39:43,713
RECOVERY STARTS
WHEN AN INDIVIDUAL ADMITS
THAT HE OR SHE HAS A PROBLEM.

540
00:39:43,782 --> 00:39:47,717
ISN'T THAT RIGHT, TODD?

541
00:39:47,785 --> 00:39:51,020
- THAT'S RIGHT.
- OH, GOD.

542
00:39:51,088 --> 00:39:55,090
LET ME TELL YOU, THE TWO OF YOU
HAVE ONE HELL OF A PROBLEM.

543
00:40:03,468 --> 00:40:05,734
<i> LISTEN, SPORT,</i>
<i> WE'RE GONNA SEE MOMMY</i>
<i> IN JUST A FEW MINUTES.</i>

544
00:40:05,803 --> 00:40:08,437
OKAY.
SO JILL WAS TELLIN'
THE WHOLE TRUTH AFTER ALL.

545
00:40:08,506 --> 00:40:11,173
I FEEL LIKE A REAL PUNK
LAYIN' INTO HER THE WAY I DID.

546
00:40:11,241 --> 00:40:14,109
HEY, YOU LIVE
AND YOU LEARN.

547
00:40:14,178 --> 00:40:18,247
YEAH, BUT I'VE DECIDED,
YOU KNOW, I'M GONNA FINISH
UP MY TIME HERE THE RIGHT WAY.

548
00:40:18,316 --> 00:40:20,883
I'VE JUST BEEN KIND OF
GOIN' THROUGH THE MOTIONS.

549
00:40:20,952 --> 00:40:23,119
I GOTTA START THINKIN'
ABOUT<i> MY</i> FUTURE.

550
00:40:23,188 --> 00:40:25,988
GOOD FOR YOU.

551
00:40:26,057 --> 00:40:28,991
THANKS A LOT, JAROD.
SOMETHIN' FOR YOU.
HEY, WHAT'S THIS?

552
00:40:29,059 --> 00:40:30,993
SKINT RABBIT.
OH, WOW.

553
00:40:31,061 --> 00:40:34,897
"BLOODY LOVE BONES." BUT
DON'T LISTEN TO IT BACKWARDS.
YOU'LL END UP HERE FOR REAL.

554
00:40:36,968 --> 00:40:39,969
THANKS FOR EVERYTHING.

555
00:40:40,037 --> 00:40:42,571
I-I HOPE I CAN
MAKE THIS UP TO JILL.

556
00:40:42,640 --> 00:40:44,773
NOW'S YOUR CHANCE.

557
00:40:46,311 --> 00:40:48,344
MOMMY!

558
00:41:00,124 --> 00:41:01,991
MOMMY, ARE WE GOING HOME NOW?

559
00:41:02,059 --> 00:41:05,361
<i>WE ARE GONNA GO HOME</i>
<i>IN TWO SECONDS, OKAY?</i>

560
00:41:07,932 --> 00:41:10,365
YOU LOOK GOOD.
I'M STARTIN' TO FEEL GOOD.

561
00:41:10,434 --> 00:41:12,501
SO WHAT NOW?

562
00:41:12,570 --> 00:41:15,371
ONE DAY AT A TIME.

563
00:41:15,439 --> 00:41:19,208
JAROD, I DON'T KNOW
HOW I COULD EVER REPAY YOU
FOR EVERYTHING YOU'VE DONE.

564
00:41:23,681 --> 00:41:26,315
THE DEBT'S
ALREADY BEEN PAID.

565
00:41:28,319 --> 00:41:30,786
THANK YOU.

566
00:41:41,865 --> 00:41:45,568
[ Phone Ringing ]
SYDNEY.

567
00:41:45,636 --> 00:41:47,636
<i> I DIDN'T THINK</i>
<i> YOU'D STILL BE WORKING.</i>

568
00:41:47,705 --> 00:41:50,739
GOOD OF YOU TO CALL.
I WAS GETTING REALLY WORRIED.

569
00:41:50,808 --> 00:41:54,309
'CAUSE YOU THOUGHT
I MIGHT HAVE SLIPPED BACK INTO
MY CHILDHOOD DRUG ADDICTION?

570
00:41:54,379 --> 00:41:57,547
JUST TELL ME WHY.
WHY DID YOU LET THEM
DO THAT TO ME?

571
00:41:57,615 --> 00:42:00,215
JAROD--

572
00:42:00,284 --> 00:42:02,652
YOU'RE THE ONLY PERSON
THAT I TRUSTED.

573
00:42:03,821 --> 00:42:06,155
YOU WERE LIKE A--

574
00:42:09,093 --> 00:42:11,026
YOU SHOULD'VE STOPPED THEM,
SYDNEY.

575
00:42:11,095 --> 00:42:13,228
JAROD, I COULDN'T.

576
00:42:14,899 --> 00:42:16,832
WHY NOT?

577
00:42:16,900 --> 00:42:19,835
BECAUSE I WAS
A TEST SUBJECT MYSELF.

578
00:42:21,472 --> 00:42:23,705
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

579
00:42:23,774 --> 00:42:26,408
I ASKED RAINES--
RATHER, I DEMANDED...

580
00:42:26,477 --> 00:42:31,079
THAT YOU BE
LEFT OUT OF THE DRUG TESTING
AND THAT THEY USE ME INSTEAD.

581
00:42:31,148 --> 00:42:33,249
AND RAINES AGREED.

582
00:42:33,317 --> 00:42:37,252
IT WAS ONLY WHEN I CAME OUT
OF DETOX THAT I REALIZED
WHAT HAD HAPPENED--

583
00:42:37,321 --> 00:42:38,887
THAT HE'D LIED.

584
00:42:42,327 --> 00:42:44,926
SO YOU SACRIFICED YOURSELF
TO PROTECT ME.

585
00:42:47,097 --> 00:42:49,699
WHY DIDN'T YOU EVER
TELL ME THAT?

586
00:42:49,767 --> 00:42:52,934
I NEVER WANTED YOU
TO FEEL OBLIGATED...

587
00:42:53,003 --> 00:42:55,737
TO STAY HERE
AT THE CENTRE...

588
00:42:55,806 --> 00:42:57,940
IF YOU HAD A CHANCE
TO GET AWAY.

589
00:42:58,009 --> 00:43:00,609
I'M SORRY, JAROD.

590
00:43:00,678 --> 00:43:03,078
I'M REALLY SORRY.

